modules.description: This module handles OAuth 2.0 authentication for Dropbox, providing functions to initiate authorization flows, extract authorization codes or tokens from URIs, and exchange codes for access tokens. It works with URIs and string-based codes or tokens, supporting both token and code-based authorization workflows. Use this module to implement user authentication and obtain access tokens for Dropbox API operations.

This module implements Dropbox's API using Cohttp_lwt_unix.Client, enabling account management, file metadata retrieval, synchronization, and file operations like copy, move, and delete with OAuth2 authentication. It handles user information, file and folder metadata, shared folder states, sync cursors, and streaming content, supporting cross-device sync, collaborative sharing, and large file handling with version control. The OAuth2 submodule manages authorization flows, token exchange, and URI-based code extraction, allowing secure user authentication and token acquisition for API access. Example uses include syncing user files across devices, managing shared folders with access controls, and streaming large file uploads with resumable transfers.
